descriptionHtml:
[img=432x301]http://static-1.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/49727-4-1389386765.jpg[/img]

[center][size=32][color=green]Swift Steeds Stables[/color][/size][/center]

[center][size=14]Featuring asymmetrical and symmetrical textures by Slof[/center][/size]



[size=15][color=red]Adds seven new stables to Skyrim[/color][/size]


[size=15][color=red]Each stable has at least 5 different horses to choose from[/color][/size]


[size=12][color=red]Cleaned with TESVEdit[/color][/size]


[size=8][color=red]Immersive Horses version now available[/color][/size]

http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/64067/?


Details

Six of the seven have one breed type (Outer Markarth Stables -- Fjord type, Outer Dragon Bridge Stables -- Friesian type, Outer Falkreath -- Arab type, Shor's Stone Stables -- Mustang type, Kynesgrove Stables -- Gypsy Vanner type, Outer Ivarstead Stables -- Newfoundland Pony type.)


One has five types for sale (Rorikstead Stables) -- Future plans are to change this to a unique horse



This is fully compatible with More Stables and Lesser Hold Stables.



There are 6 free stallions and 7 free mares with their foals you can find. The added stables have clues (letters and/or journals) -- look inside the tent on the table. (if you don't see anything there, check the stable owner's chest or knapsack.) A couple of the vanilla stables have clues too -- look for a strongbox outside the stable owner's house called 'Letters'. (You can take any clues you find without stealing.)

All the mares and stallions have papers and a short explanation as to why they're abandoned. Most of them also have leveled and unique items on or near their deceased owners or deceased owner's knapsacks.

Most of the horses only have one clue, a couple have clues that lead you to more clues if you need them.

You can just take the horses without getting their papers or finding clues. I've tried to make the horses difficult to find, but it's not exactly easy to hide something as large as a horse. :) You might stumble across them without ever seeing a clue.

Mares and foals will follow each other and should be together. Search the area the clue indicates/states. Horses sometimes rush towards or away from danger.

Having trouble finding the horses?  kichigaikikyokagome made a guide  http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/69445/?


[size=8][color=red]Permissions[/color][/size]

--All textures and stallion bits belong to Slof. You must see her website Slof's Hive for permissions

For the mare and filly meshes
--You may not use any of my meshes in a mod you're charging for -- No exceptions


--You don't need my permission to use them, just credit me for my work.


[size=8]Credits[/size]

Thanks to all the wonderful modders who provide resources and tutorials
Slof for the beautiful new horse textures (Slofslair)
Rebel O'conner for remapping the vanilla mesh
Hanaisse (Tes Alliance) for the 'Creating Armor in Skyrim' tutorial and Blank Roadsigns.
Dark Rider (Tes Alliance) for the 'My First Stable' tutorial
Tamara for the Stroti rescources
Runspect for the Resources for Modders
Meo for the tents
Blary for the Open Books
BrettM for FPI Experiment pack 1
Oaristys and Tony67 Modder's Resource pack
Insanitysorrow for the Readme generator the Readme is based on
Jokerine for the blank inn sign
kichigaikikyokagome for the guide to finding the horses
KoscheiTheDruidBoy -- Saddle mash up
mistickhybrid -- Horse Armors for Skyrim (textures and part of the mesh)  http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/13348/?
Zira's Skyrim Horse base -- textures by Zira   http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/19710/?


And thanks to the people who make the software
Bethesda for creating Skyrim and the Creation Kit.
Blender, Paint.net, Nifscope and GIMP developers for providing free software.

files.name: Swift Steeds Stables
files.changelogHtml:
Mares and foals from the Rift farm will now stay where you put them (I hope)
All horses now have a hold position AI package meaning they should all stay exactly or very close to where you leave them
All horses are now invulnerable
Shor's stone stable has been moved a little off the road for better compatibility with ETAC
All versions of the mod are now fully compatible with ETAC
Added Immersive Horses version
